cs.CR, cs.IT, cs.CC, cs.SY, cs.DS

This paper is about a cryptanalysis attack on a key encapsulation mechanism, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The attack is based on solving a system of polynomial equations, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and computational complexity (cs.CC). The authors also mention the use of Gröbner basis, which is a tool from algebraic geometry and symbolic computation, making categories cs.SY and cs.DS likely as well.
